reviews.review_text: Thank you, for a real good time! Cool show, good song selection. Sound quality here seems to change a few times. I drove down from Pittsburgh after seeing Phish for the 1st time the night before. What a gorgeous autumn drive it was! I've had sbd tapes of this show said to be made from patching into the venue's audio system, but I don't know. This was a pretty solid show, I think my 3rd of 3 HSF's and it was a good one. Jerry sounds a little tired on Terrapin, but a good jam ensues. Space was pretty nice, Phil goes off for a while! Post-Drumz was strong too. After the show, some guy in the lot got in an empty golf cart & crashed right into a crowd of people like 10 feet away! This was one of the few venues where I witnessed the police mounted on horses, like dozens of them here & there. Crazy. Anyway, caught a few zzz's at a rest stop going home & woke to another beautiful, frost covered autumn wonderland. See you in'95, Boyz.
Favorite Aiko Aiko! Aiko Aiko is sooo good :)

I am on an amazing journey I am listening to every 1994 show in order, mining for gold. 

This soundboard doesn't sound like it's in stereo? Also sounds like they might have layered some effects on the vocals?

Jer gets lost in a couple of songs and there are some occasional timing issues, but this is one solid show. 

Set 1 Highlights: Do not miss the Iko opener. Probably the best of '94. Loose Lucy is always fun, but Jerry really belts out of the vocals. 

Set 2 Highlights: Help>Slip>Frank>Estimated>Terrapin. Duh.
